OL,3,CMinimum wage to rise in Guernsey from
OL,4,COctober
OL,6,FThe Economic Development Committee
OL,7,FPresident, Deputy Neil Inder, and
OL,8,Ffellow member Deputy Simon Vermeulen
OL,9,Fcalled for a smaller rise in the
OL,10,Fminimum wage to either #11.25 or
OL,11,F#11.55 but this was defeated.
OL,13,FProposals to increase the adult
OL,14,Fminimum wage were mooted in February
OL,15,Fas members of the public were invited
OL,16,Fto share their views, with plans to
OL,17,Fbring it up from 60% to 66% of average
OL,18,Fearnings by 2030.
